history.content: That schedule seems manageable. 168 and 188 are two of the lowest workload upper division classes purely from a quantity perspective not in terms of concepts or exam studying with 168 (1 midterm, 3 projects/hw [average 20 hrs], 1 final). There will definitely be project deadline overlap, but just make sure you stay on top of your deadlines by starting early and looking to find study/project friends.

I know I want to take 61C and 168 forsure. Just curious if adding 188 would be overkill in terms of workload. I'm guessing that since all 3 are project-based, there's a high chance there will be project deadlines close together at at least one point in the semester, which would be difficult to manage.
history.subject: Workload of CS 168 + 61C + 188?
